Jab router on hota hai (power lagate hi), uska process kuch aise hota hai:

1ï¸âƒ£ POST (Power-On Self Test)

        English: Router checks its hardware (RAM, CPU, interfaces).
        
        Hindi: Jaise computer start hote hi apna hardware check karta hai, router bhi apne parts ko test karta hai.
        ğŸ‘‰ Agar hardware kharab ho â†’ error message aayega.

2ï¸âƒ£ Bootstrap Program Load

        English: Bootstrap is a small code stored in ROM. It decides what to do next (like a guide).
        
        Hindi: Bootstrap ek chhota software hai jo router ko batata hai ki Operating System (IOS) kaha se load karna hai.

3ï¸âƒ£ Load IOS (Internetwork Operating System)

        English: Router now loads the IOS (its brain) from Flash memory (or TFTP server if needed).
        
        Hindi: Ab router apna IOS software load karta hai jo usko chalata hai. Ye mostly Flash memory me hota hai.

4ï¸âƒ£ Find Configuration File

        English: Router looks for a configuration file (startup-config) in NVRAM.
        
        Hindi: Router check karta hai ki koi settings/configuration file hai kya NVRAM me (jaise IP addresses, routing info).

5ï¸âƒ£ Run Configuration

        English: If config file is found â†’ router applies settings.
        
        Hindi: Agar file mil gayi â†’ router wahi purani settings load karega (IP, routes, passwords).
ğŸ‘‰ Agar config file nahi mili â†’ router setup mode me chala jayega (basic configuration karne ko bolega).

